com.camerontec.catalys.server.collection

Class PersistentBlockingQueueBase<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.collection.PersistentBlockingQueueBase<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The element type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPeekableBlockingQueue<E>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, BlockingQueue<E>, Queue<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoundedPersistentBlockingQueue, UnboundedPersistentBlockingQueue

    public abstract class PersistentBlockingQueueBase<E>
extends Object
implements IPeekableBlockingQueue<E>
    Base class for persistent java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue implementations.

    This implements the java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue contract while delegating implementation specifics to its subclasses.

    Not all java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue methods are supported as it would be potentially dangerous and certainly inefficient to do so. Specifically, the following methods are not supported and will throw java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException if called:

    • toArray()
    • toArray(Object[])
    • containsAll(Collection)
    • removeAll(Collection)
    • retainAll(Collection)
    • remove(Object o)
    • contains(Object o)
    • drainTo(Collection)

    Non-mutating, thread safe, iteration over the queue is supported. Iteration behavior in the presence of concurrent modification is implementation dependent.

    The underlying persistent collection is obtained from the ICollectionRegistry in its implementation. Collections obtained in this way are automatically HA aware when running in HA context. However, performance is degraded in that case. This implementation makes no guarantees regarding the performance difference between usage in a non HA context versus usage in an HA context other than it tries to be as efficient as possible.

    For maximum serialization/deserialization performance when the element is not a trivial type consider supplying a custom element IBytesSegmentExternalizer via the appropriate subclass constructor.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PersistentBlockingQueueBase

        protected PersistentBlockingQueueBase(Properties properties,
                                      Class<E> elementClass,
                                      IBytesSegmentExternalizer<E> elementExternalizer)
                               throws IllegalArgumentException,
                                      NameNotFoundException,
                                      IOException
        Constructor.

        At least one of elementClass and elementExternalizer must be supplied. If both are supplied then the elementExternalizer takes precedence when constructing the underlying persistent storage.

        Parameters:
        properties - The persistent queue properties. May not be null. At a minimum the CollectionProperties.DIRECTORY_NAME property must be specified.
        elementClass - The element's class. May be null provided elementExternalizer is supplied.
        elementExternalizer - The element's externalizer. May be null provided elementClass is supplied.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - On one or more invalid arguments.
        NameNotFoundException - On failure to locate the collection registry service.
        IOException - On error initializing the underlying persistence.
        See Also:
        CollectionProperties
